<TITLE> Germany keeper Neuer to make debut against UAE </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BERLIN, June 2 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Talented Schalke 04 keeper Manuel Neuer will win his first international cap on Tuesday when he starts in Germany's friendly match against the United Arab Emirates, coach Joachim Loew told reporters on Monday. Loew has still to pick his first choice keeper one year before the 2010 World Cup in South Africa, with Hanover's Robert Enke, Rene Adler from Bayer Leverkusen, Werder Bremen's Tim Wiese and 23-year-old Neuer in the running for the spot
